- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper involves analyzing bibliographic data and predicting research areas of authors. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper deals with analyzing co-authorship networks. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category as the paper involves working with a bibliographic network. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper uses state-of-the-art network embedding methods.
